  "text": "The retrovirus vector pBabe-GFP was prepared by inserting the EGFP cDNA from pEGFP-N1 and an internal ribosomal entry site from pCIN4 [CITATION_1] . The pBabe-c-FLIP-GFP was prepared by inserting the human c-FLIP cDNA (encoding the long form of c-FLIP protein) into pBabe-GFP. The human c-FLIP cDNA was modified to express the N-terminal Flag tag. Phoenix cells [CITATION_2] were split at 1:4 in 10-cm dishes in DMEM-10% FBS. After 24 h, cells were transfected with 20 g of retrovirus vector by lipofectAmine 2000 reagent (Invitrogen, Carlsbad, CA). The medium was changed, 48 h after transfection, to RPMI 1640-10% FBS. After an additional 12 h, virus-containing supernatant was collected and filtered through a 0.45-m membrane, and the medium was supplemented with 8 g/ml polybrene (Sigma). LNCaP cells were split at 1:3 in 10-cm dishes 1 d before infection. Cells were incubated with retrovirus for 36 h and split at 1:3 in 10-cm dishes. Cells were selected with 2 g/ml puromycin (Sigma) for 6 d (ϳ80-90% confluence). All the selected cells were GFP positive. The cells were split at 1:3 and grown in RPMI 1640-10% FBS supplemented with 2 g/ml puromycin (Sigma) for 4-5 d.",
